exercise:
This card snaps up instantly on hover but should glide both in AND out over 0.2s. Fix it and explain what was wrong:

.card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
  transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}

solution:
.card {
  transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}

.card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
}

The bug: transition was declared only inside :hover, so it only applies while hovering. Mouse-in animates, but on mouse-out the :hover rule (and its transition) vanish, so the card snaps back. Declaring transition on the base .card rule makes it apply in both directions.

