exercise:
This renders a username from your API. Find the vulnerability, name the attack, and rewrite it safely:

var badge = document.createElement("span");
badge.innerHTML = "sending as " + user.username;
header.appendChild(badge);

solution:
Vulnerability: user.username goes through innerHTML, so a username containing HTML (e.g. <img src=x onerror=alert(1)>) gets parsed and executed. The attack is XSS (cross-site scripting).

Safe version:

var badge = document.createElement("span");
badge.textContent = "sending as " + user.username;
header.appendChild(badge);

textContent treats the whole string as literal text, exactly like the sendingAs line in script.js does.

