solution:
It logs: got: { error: "nope" }

fetch resolves on ANY HTTP response, including 404, so the success path runs and the error body is treated as data. The catch only fires on network-level failure.

Fix, same as loadNews() does:

fetch("/api/missing")
  .then(function (r) {
    if (!r.ok) throw new Error("status " + r.status);
    return r.json();
  })
  .then(function (data) { console.log("got:", data); })
  .catch(function (e) { console.log("failed:", e.message); });

